                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/325: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Marseille</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marseille</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-03T10:00:00+00:00"
                            >April 3, 1937—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 3—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s April 2, 7 p.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d442fn54">Not printed; it
                        instructed the Consul General to cable charges on which prisoners were held
                        (852.2221/317).</note> Prisoners charged with violation of French law of
                    January 21, 1937, and the ministerial decree of February 18, 1937,<note n="55"
                        xml:id="d442fn55">See telegrams No. 89, January 22, 2 p.m., and No. 242,
                        February 19, 1 p.m., from the Ambassador in France, <ref target="#pg_231"
                            >pp. 231</ref> and <ref target="#pg_479">479</ref>.</note> by having
                    passed in transit through French territory en route to Spain in order to enroll
                    in the forces fighting there. The French press states that prisoners have now
                    admitted to the French authorities that this was their intention. Full report by
                        mail.<note n="56" xml:id="d442fn56">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
